This workbench can be installed from the [[Std_AddonMgr|Addon Manager]]. For manual installation see [[Installing_more_workbenches|Installing more workbenches]].
</div>

<span id="Tools"></span>
==Инструменты==

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
The Sheet Metal tools are all located in the {{MenuCommand|Sheet Metal}} menu and the '''Sheet Metal''' toolbar that appear when you load the SheetMetal Workbench.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* [[Image:SheetMetal_AddBase.svg|32px]] [[SheetMetal_AddBase|Make Base Wall]]: Creates a sheet metal base object from a sketch, either a profile or a plate.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* [[Image:SheetMetal_AddWall.svg|32px]] [[SheetMetal_AddWall|Make Wall]]: Adds a flange on each selected edge of a base plate. (The flange can be turned into a hem by modifying its angle.)
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* [[Image:SheetMetal_Extrude.svg|32px]] [[SheetMetal_Extrude|Extend Face]]: Extends a sheet metal plate at a selected edge face along its normal.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* [[Image:SheetMetal_ExtendBySketch.svg|32px]] [[SheetMetal_ExtendBySketch|Extend by Sketch]]: Extends a sheet metal plate at a selected edge face by adding an outline sketch. It can be used to create interlocking geometry. (This was split from the above tool and is available in version 0.7.57 and newer)
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* [[Image:SheetMetal_AddFoldWall.svg|32px]] [[SheetMetal_AddFoldWall|Fold a Wall]]: Folds a face at a chosen line with a specified bend radius.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* [[Image:SheetMetal_Unfold.svg|32px]] [[SheetMetal_Unfold|Unfold]]: Flattens a folded sheet metal object and generates an unfold solid and an outline sketch with bend lines (provides a dialog to set parameters).
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* [[Image:SheetMetal_UnattendedUnfold.svg|32px]] [[SheetMetal_UnattendedUnfold|Unattended Unfold]]: Flattens a folded sheet metal object and generates an unfold solid and an outline sketch with bend lines (if parameters have already been set).
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* [[Image:SheetMetal_UnfoldUpdate.svg|32px]] [[SheetMetal_UnfoldUpdate|Unfold Update]]: Updates all unfold objects.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* [[Image:SheetMetal_AddCornerRelief.svg|32px]] [[SheetMetal_AddCornerRelief|Add Corner Relief]]: Adds a corner relief to a corner.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* [[Image:SheetMetal_AddRelief.svg|32px]] [[SheetMetal_AddRelief|Make Relief]]: 1st step to convert a shell object into an unfoldable sheet metal object, adds a relief (cutout) to a corner.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* [[Image:SheetMetal_AddJunction.svg|32px]] [[SheetMetal_AddJunction|Make Junction]]: 2nd step to convert a shell object into an unfoldable sheet metal object, creates an open junction on the edge of two walls.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* [[Image:SheetMetal_AddBend.svg|32px]] [[SheetMetal_AddBend|Make Bend]]: 3rd step to convert a shell object into an unfoldable sheet metal object, replaces sharp edges with round bends.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* [[Image:SheetMetal_SketchOnSheet.svg|32px]] [[SheetMetal_SketchOnSheet|Sketch On Sheet metal]]: Cuts a sketch based hole pattern along the folded walls of a sheet metal object.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* [[Image:SheetMetal_AddCutout.svg|32px]] [[SheetMetal_AddCutout|Extruded Cutout]]: Creates an extruded cutout from a sketch extrusion.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* [[Image:SheetMetal_Forming.svg|32px]] [[SheetMetal_Forming|Make Forming in Wall]]: Embosses shapes with or without holes into a sheet metal plate.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* [[Image:SheetMetal_BaseShape.svg|32px]] [[SheetMetal_BaseShape|Add base shape]]: Adds a basic sheet metal object from parameters (introduced in version 0.3.10).
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==Brief description==
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
This workbench provides tools for the two main tasks: 
* Create sheet metal objects 
* Unfold sheet metal objects
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
This section is meant to give a rough idea of how to use the supplied tools. More detailed information can be found on each tool's own page (see above) or in the linked tutorials (see below).
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
===Create a sheet metal object===
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
====Start with a profile====
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
# Create an open polyline (preferably with the [[Sketcher_Workbench|Sketcher Workbench]])
# Use the [[Image:SheetMetal_AddBase.svg|16px]] [[SheetMetal_AddBase|Make Base Wall]] command to create a sheet metal profile.
</div> 

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
====Start with a blank====
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
# Create a closed polyline (preferably with the sketcher)
# Use the [[Image:SheetMetal_AddBase.svg|16px]] [[SheetMetal_AddBase|Make Base Wall]] command to create a sheet metal blank.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
====Start with a base shape====
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
# Use the [[Image:SheetMetal_BaseShape.svg|16px]] [[SheetMetal_BaseShape|Add base shape]] comand to add a basic sheet metal object from parameters (introduced in version 0.3.10).
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
====Start with a solid shape====
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Alternatively a blank and a profile shape can be created with tools of the [[Image:Workbench_Part.svg|16px]] [[Part_Workbench|Part Workbench]] or [[Image:Workbench_PartDesign.svg|16px]] [[PartDesign_Workbench|PartDesign Workbench]].
* [[Part_Workbench|Part Workbench]]:
*# Create a [[File:Part_Extrude.svg|16px]] [[Part_Extrude|Part Extrude]] from a closed 2D wire such as a [[File:Draft_Rectangle.svg|16px]] [[Draft_Rectangle|Draft Rectangle]], a [[File:Draft_Wire.svg|16px]] [[Draft_Wire|Draft Wire]], or a [[File:Sketcher_NewSketch.svg|16px]] [[Sketcher_NewSketch|Sketch]].
*: Depending on the 2D wire shape and the extrusion length this creates a blank or a profile.
* [[PartDesign_Workbench|PartDesign Workbench]]:
*# Create a [[File:PartDesign_Body.svg|16px]] [[PartDesign_Body|PartDesign Body]]
*# Create a closed [[File:Sketcher_NewSketch.svg|16px]] [[Sketcher NewSketch|Sketch]].
*# Create a  [[File:PartDesign_Pad.svg|16px]] [[PartDesign_Pad|PartDesign Pad]] from the sketch.
*: Depending on the sketch shape and pad height this creates a blank or a profile.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Already folded shapes require hollow shapes to be transformed into unfoldable sheet metal shapes by adding some gaps or connections between their walls:
# Create a hollow shape:
#* [[Part_Workbench|Part Workbench]]:
## Create a [[File:Part_Extrude.svg|16px]] [[Part_Extrude|Part Extrude]] as above, or use a primitive like a [[File:Part_Box.svg|16px]] [[Part_Box|Part Box]] instead.
## Use [[File:Part_Thickness.svg|16px]] [[Part_Thickness|Part Thickness]] to obtain a hollow shape of constant thickness.
#* [[PartDesign_Workbench|PartDesign Workbench]]:
## Create a [[File:PartDesign_Pad.svg|16px]] [[PartDesign_Pad|PartDesign Pad]] as above, or use a primitive like a [[File:PartDesign_AdditiveBox.svg|16px]] [[PartDesign_AdditiveBox|PartDesign AdditiveBox]].
## Use [[Image:PartDesign_Thickness.svg|16px]] [[PartDesign_Thickness|PartDesign Thickness]] to obtain a hollow shape of constant thickness.
# Adding gaps and connections to the edged shape:
## Use [[Image:SheetMetal_AddRelief.svg|16px]] [[SheetMetal_AddRelief|Make Relief]] to cut off selected corners.
## Use [[Image:SheetMetal_AddJunction.svg|16px]] [[SheetMetal_AddJunction|Make Junction]] to create junctions with gaps between adjoining walls that need to be disjoined.
## Use [[Image:SheetMetal_AddBend.svg|16px]] [[SheetMetal_AddBend|Make Bend]] to create cylindrical connections for the remaining walls that need to stay joined.
# Check if the resulting sheet metal object can be unfolded. (see [[#Unfold_a_sheet_metal_object|Unfold...]] below).
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
If you start modeling a sheet metal shape in a [[File:PartDesign_Body.svg|16px]] [[PartDesign_Body|PartDesign Body]], you can mix SheetMetal features with PartDesign features such as [[File:PartDesign_Pocket.svg|16px]] [[PartDesign_Pocket|PartDesign Pocket]] or [[File:PartDesign_Hole.svg|16px]] [[PartDesign_Hole|PartDesign Hole]].
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
====Adding more features====
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
The unfoldable basic sheet metal shape can be extended:
# Use [[Image:SheetMetal_Extrude.svg|16px]] [[SheetMetal_Extrude|Extend Face]] to enlarge walls.
# Use [[Image:SheetMetal_ExtendBySketch.svg|16px]] [[SheetMetal_ExtendBySketch|Extend by Sketch]] to partially extend walls and optionally create interlocking geometry. ({{VersionPlus|V0.7.57}})
# Use [[Image:SheetMetal_AddWall.svg|16px]] [[SheetMetal_AddWall|Make Wall]] to add new flanges or hems to the existing shape.
# Use [[Image:SheetMetal_AddCornerRelief.svg|16px]] [[SheetMetal_AddCornerRelief|Add Corner Relief]] to add or reshape corner reliefs.
# Use [[Image:SheetMetal_AddFoldWall.svg|16px]] [[SheetMetal_AddFoldWall|Fold a Wall]] to fold a wall at a chosen line, i.e. it will trimm a wall at said line, relocate the cut away side, and rejoin them with a cylindrical connection.
# Use [[Image:SheetMetal_SketchOnSheet.svg|16px]] [[SheetMetal_SketchOnSheet|Sketch on Sheet metal]] to cut holes into the shape starting on a chosen wall and then following the adjoined walls and connections.
# Use [[Image:SheetMetal_AddCutout.svg|16px]] [[SheetMetal_AddCutout|Extruded Cutout]] to cut oblique holes but obtain perpendicular edge faces that do not prevent the shape from being unfolded.
# Use [[Image:SheetMetal_Forming.svg|16px]] [[SheetMetal_Forming|Make Forming in Wall]] to stamp a shape into a plate (wall).
:: After the creation of a WallForming feature the SheetMetal object is '''no longer unfoldable'''!
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Some parameters will be inherited from the parent object(s) but it is better to check the relevant parameters at each stage.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Several tools from other workbenches can be used to add holes or to reshape edges.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
===Unfold a sheet metal object===
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
To unfold a sheet metal object activate the [[Image:SheetMetal_Unfold.svg|16px]] [[SheetMetal_Unfold|Unfold]] or the [[Image:SheetMetal_UnattendedUnfold.svg|16px]] [[SheetMetal_UnattendedUnfold|Unattended Unfold]] tool.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
The result will be a 3D object with an optional outline sketch including bend lines.
</div>

